  "paragraphs": [
    {
      "paragraph_name": "FUNC-CODES",
      "summary": null,
      "purpose": "This data structure defines a set of constants representing IMS (Information Management System) function codes. These codes are used to specify the type of operation to be performed against an IMS database. Each function code is a 4-character alphanumeric field (PIC X(04)) and is assigned a specific value. The function codes include 'GU  ' (Get Unique), 'GHU ' (Get Hold Unique), 'GN  ' (Get Next), 'GHN ' (Get Hold Next), 'GNP ' (Get Next within Parent), 'GHNP' (Get Hold Next within Parent), 'REPL' (Replace), 'ISRT' (Insert), and 'DLET' (Delete). These codes are used in conjunction with IMS calls to retrieve, update, and delete data within the IMS database. The structure is defined in working storage and does not directly interact with input or output files, but rather provides symbolic constants for use in other parts of the program that interact with IMS.",
      "called_by": [],
